    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Compared with traditional development methods, with low-code tools, you can create data science models, workflows, and applications without having to write a lot of code. This makes the development process faster and less complex. There are also other advantages:</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><ol><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Increased Accessibility: Low-code tools make data science more accessible to a wider range of users, including non-technical users, by simplifying the development process.</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Better Collaboration: These tools often have built-in collaboration features, making it easier for teams to work together on data science projects.</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Improved Agility: Low-code tools are often more flexible and adaptable than traditional data science tools, allowing organizations to quickly respond to changing business needs.</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Lower Costs: By reducing the amount of custom code required, low-code tools can also help lower costs and reduce the risk of errors in data science projects.</li></ol></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">The rise of no-code/low-code machine learning platforms (and libraries) has accelerated data science-related development. With the help of these platforms and frameworks, data scientists can achieve a better balance between heavy data research and extensive programming tasks.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">In this article, I summarize the most valuable Python-based low-code machine learning libraries, covering the most popular subjects of data science — data exploration and mining, machine learning, and deep learning.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
